{
  "texts": [
    "Despite these advantages, AI may be limited by the variability in image quality and the presence of artifacts, which can affect the accuracy of segmentation, especially for teeth.",
    "For example, many teeth in each arch can significantly complicate the segmentation process, especially when crowding is present.",
    "In addition, the tooth is a component made up of several tissues (cement, dentin, pulp, and enamel) that are close to various anatomical structures.",
    "Not all CBCT scanners can detect by the geographic concentration and variation in radiograph readers' experience.",
    "Nonetheless, the lack of high-quality studies and the variation in AI performance point to the necessity for more investigation."
  ]
}